se></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528622\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528622\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 08, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ind1665702879378.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ind1665702879378.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ind1665702879378.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ind1665702879378\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                 \n DBMS Assignments\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">DBMS assignments define the route to a database via a DBMS connector. During installation, two paths ($DBMS and $DBMS_DEF) are configured for default SQLite databases, but these can be replaced by path assignments to the actual databases used in your environment.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ind1665702879378__section_w7234ab1b5b1_w7235ab1b5_w7236ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d937713e51\">\n                  \n Two-Path Structure\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ind1665702879378__p_d30176e1_d30177e1_d30178e1\">Once you have defined a DBMS path assignment, you can direct other paths to it. For example, you could define a path to a MySQL database, and then assign the Repository paths to this new $MQL path:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[PATHS}\n$MY_MQL= MQL:host:database|username|password\n$IDF= $MY_MQL\n$SYS= $MY_MQL\n$UUU= $MY_MQL\n$DEF= $MY_MQL\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ind1665702879378__p_d30179e1_d30180e1_d30181e1\">This two-path structure (path-to-connector, and then path-to-path) enables you to:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ind1665702879378__li_d15296e1_d15297e1_d15298e1\">Minimize the number of paths to the DBMS that are open at any one time. This can be important for a DBMS that has a limited number of open channels or logons available.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ind1665702879378__li_d15299e1_d15300e1_d15301e1\">Switch several paths to another DBMS or network with only one assignment, for example, by changing $DEF from $DBMS_DEF to $MY_SQL.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ind1665702879378__section_w7237ab1b5b3_w7238ab1b5_w7239ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d937713e75\">\n                  \n Paths for Entity Data\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ind1665702879378__p_d30185e1_d30186e1_d30187e1\">Each entity definition specifies a default DBMS to store data, and is assigned to one of the default paths that was created during installation, for example $DBMS_DEF.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ind1665702879378__p_d30188e1_d30189e1_d30190e1\">A typical working situation involves many types of users and situations, so you will often find that the default assignment in the entity definition is not sufficient.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ind1665702879378__p_d30191e1_d30192e1_d30193e1\">You can use assignments in either a local or a global assignment file to direct entities to another connector or to give another name to an entity. The paths used in these assignments can be paths that were established during the installation process or your own user-defined paths.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528622\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528622\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "DBMS Assignments Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 08, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 DBMS Assignments DBMS assignments define the route to a database via a DBMS connector. During installation, two paths ($DBMS and $DBMS_DEF) are configured for default SQLite databases, but these can be replaced by path assignments to the actual databases used in your environment. Two-Path Structure Once you have defined a DBMS path assignment, you can direct other paths to it. For example, you could define a path to a MySQL database, and then assign the Repository paths to this new $MQL path: [PATHS} $MY_MQL= MQL:host:database|username|password $IDF= $MY_MQL $SYS= $MY_MQL $UUU= $MY_MQL $DEF= $MY_MQL Copy This two-path structure (path-to-connector, and then path-to-path) enables you to: Minimize the number of paths to the DBMS that are open at any one time. This can be important for a DBMS that has a limited number of open channels or logons available. Switch several paths to another DBMS or network with only one assignment, for example, by changing $DEF from $DBMS_DEF to $MY_SQL. Paths for Entity Data Each entity definition specifies a default DBMS to store data, and is assigned to one of the default paths that was created during installation, for example $DBMS_DEF. A typical working situation involves many types of users and situations, so you will often find that the default assignment in the entity definition is not sufficient. You can use assignments in either a local or a global assignment file to direct entities to another connector or to give another name to an entity. The paths used in these assignments can be paths that were established during the installation process or your own user-defined paths. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}